modules.description: Converts Windows error codes into human-readable strings. Works with the `Win_error_t.t` enumerated type representing system error codes. Useful for logging or displaying descriptive error messages when handling system-level operations on Windows platforms.

This module defines a comprehensive set of error codes corresponding to Windows system errors. It includes variants for handling specific OS-level failures such as file access issues, resource contention, invalid handles, and network or device errors. These values are used directly in system call error handling and low-level resource management scenarios.

This module converts Windows system error codes into human-readable strings and provides mappings from Unix error types to Windows-specific errors. It works with the `Unix.error` type and a custom `t` type representing specific Windows errors. Use this when handling system-level errors on Windows platforms, such as interpreting file or network operation failures.

Converts integer error codes to corresponding values in the `Win_error_t` enumerated type. It operates on raw integers and returns an optional `Win_error_t.t` value, allowing safe mapping of system-level error codes to structured error types. This is useful when handling Windows API errors where integer codes must be translated into meaningful error states for validation or logging.
